         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="0012_002414_000206_0001.jpg" xml:id="d4e39"/>
            <p>5th Month May 18, 1809</p>
            <p>John Dickinson</p>
            <p>Acknowledging Rect of</p>
            <p>Certificate of $2,000 at</p>
            <p>his Credit in Bank North America</p>
            <p>PAID</p>
            <p>Charles Petit Esquire</p>
            <p>Philadelphia</p>
            <p>paid</p>
            <pb n="2" facs="0012_002414_000206_0002.jpg" xml:id="d4e59"/>
            <p>My respected Friend,</p>
            <p>My Letter of the Second insland, with a copy of a certificate that I have credit in the Bank of North America for two thousand Dollars deposited by the Insurance Company of North America, is received and I thank thee for thy promptness and kind attentions to the Business on which We have lately corresponded.</p>
            <p>I am very sincerely thy friend,</p>
            <p>Jony Dickinson</p>
            <p>Wilmington</p>
            <p>The 18th of the 5 Month</p>
            <p>1804</p>
            <p>Charles Petit Esquire</p>
            <p>Philadelphia</p>
         </div>
      </body>
